00:10:57,104 --> 00:10:59,174
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Apparently, his racing
is something in-between.</b></font>

148
00:10:59,174 --> 00:11:05,274
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Huh? In-between drift and grip?
So it's neither of the two?</b></font>

149
00:11:04,944 --> 00:11:07,904
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="66"><b>{\an5}"Steep Curve"</b></font>

150
00:11:08,614 --> 00:11:14,114
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Everyone seems to think Jo's one-handed
steer is some off-the-wall technique,</b></font>

151
00:11:14,114 --> 00:11:17,224
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but it's grounded in solid principles.</b></font>

152
00:11:17,224 --> 00:11:21,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What it boils down to is, how do you
turn along a slight steering angle?</b></font>

153
00:11:21,424 --> 00:11:26,054
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Jo has spent more than 20 years
pursuin' that question.</b></font>

154
00:11:39,974 --> 00:11:44,484
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He's combined various techniques,
and after all that trial and error,</b></font>

155
00:11:44,484 --> 00:11:47,314
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>he got to where he is now.</b></font>

156
00:11:47,314 --> 00:11:53,784
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He'll emphatically say it's not drift
and it's not grip, but if ya ask me...</b></font>

157
00:11:58,234 --> 00:12:01,224
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>...it's the perfect drift.</b></font>

158
00:12:30,464 --> 00:12:33,994
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The really high-level techniques
are the ones that're hard to see,</b></font>

159
00:12:33,994 --> 00:12:37,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and just look sort of plain.</b></font>

160
00:12:37,004 --> 00:12:39,174
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Tires do their best work</b></font>

161
00:12:39,174 --> 00:12:44,644
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>when the G-forces kick in and you're
not sure if they'll grip or slide out.</b></font>

162
00:12:44,644 --> 00:12:46,014
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah...</b></font>

163
00:12:46,014 --> 00:12:50,644
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I think he makes his car slide just
enough that you can't tell by looking.</b></font>

164
00:12:50,644 --> 00:12:54,054
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>From a logical standpoint,
that sort of makes sense.</b></font>

165
00:12:54,054 --> 00:13:00,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I get it. So that's what it means
to be in between drift and grip?</b></font>

166
00:13:01,724 --> 00:13:04,164
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Mr. Toudou knows full well.</b></font>

167
00:13:04,164 --> 00:13:08,664
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The Toudou School and Purple Shadow
have been rivals for many years.</b></font>

168
00:13:08,664 --> 00:13:11,234
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Back when we were active in the scene,</b></font>

169
00:13:11,234 --> 00:13:14,804
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>we used to have racing meets
all the time on the circuits.</b></font>

170
00:13:14,804 --> 00:13:18,644
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>To think that the top members of Purple
Shadow would actually do a street race...</b></font>

171
00:13:18,644 --> 00:13:24,014
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If we'd let this chance slip by us,
we'd never get a second one.</b></font>

172
00:13:24,014 --> 00:13:26,744
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The God Foot Kozo Hoshino...</b></font>

173
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:32,724
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>...and the God Arm Toshiya Joshima are two
men whose racing we should watch closely,</b></font>

174
00:13:32,724 --> 00:13:34,714
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'd say this means.</b></font>

175
00:13:36,864 --> 00:13:41,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Fumihiro, do you remember
Shingo Shoji of the Night Kids,</b></font>

176
00:13:41,934 --> 00:13:44,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>whose specialty was the
duct tape death match?</b></font>

177
00:13:44,934 --> 00:13:49,574
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Shoji... Oh, I think he was the guy</b></font>

178
00:13:49,574 --> 00:13:53,204
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>who'd fasten his right hand to
the steering wheel with duct tape.</b></font>

179
00:13:55,844 --> 00:13:59,854
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>This would let him turn only within
a set range of steering angles.</b></font>

180
00:13:59,854 --> 00:14:03,724
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>In other words, his turns had to
rely on accelerator handling.</b></font>

181
00:14:03,724 --> 00:14:07,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It could be that Toshiya Joshima's
single-handed steer</b></font>

182
00:14:07,424 --> 00:14:10,884
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>is an extension of that technique...</b></font>

183
00:14:13,694 --> 00:14:19,104
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Or rather, its ultimate,
most thoroughly perfected form.</b></font>

184
00:14:19,104 --> 00:14:24,074
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>But why bother? Aside from having his
left hand able to perform all shifting,</b></font>

185
00:14:24,074 --> 00:14:26,214
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>what's the benefit?</b></font>

186
00:14:26,214 --> 00:14:31,814
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The answer to that is in the realm of
sensitivity unique to Toshiya Joshima.</b></font>

187
00:14:31,814 --> 00:14:35,724
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>While undoubtedly an
unorthodox driving style,</b></font>

188
00:14:35,724 --> 00:14:41,094
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>some of the WRC's top drivers
have utilized a single-handed steer.</b></font>

189
00:14:48,064 --> 00:14:50,964
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's exactly the same! This feeling...</i></b></font>

190
00:14:50,964 --> 00:14:54,234
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>A pressure, a kind of</i>
<i>overwhelming tingling sensation.</i></b></font>

191
00:14:54,234 --> 00:14:57,444
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's just like that of a certain bastard</i>
<i>of an old man who drives an Impreza...</i></b></font>

192
00:14:57,444 --> 00:14:59,804
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>It's so alike it makes me sick!</i></b></font>

193
00:15:22,764 --> 00:15:25,704
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="66"><b>{\an5}"Touge Tunnel Project</b></font>

194
00:15:22,764 --> 00:15:25,704
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="66"><b>{\an5}To be implemented soon"</b></font>

195
00:15:24,264 --> 00:15:25,934
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What I think about how it's going?</b></font>

196
00:15:25,934 --> 00:15:27,134
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yes.</b></font>

197
00:15:27,134 --> 00:15:29,444
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That's neither here nor there.</b></font>

198
00:15:29,444 --> 00:15:32,014
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>This won't be a race that'll be
decided in one or two rounds.</b></font>

199
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,444
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Oh, really?</b></font>

200
00:15:33,444 --> 00:15:39,484
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The course itself isn't that long, and
there aren't many proper straightaways.</b></font>

201
00:15:39,484 --> 00:15:43,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's going to have to be
something of a drawn-out race.</b></font>

202
00:15:43,554 --> 00:15:45,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>But if...</b></font>

203
00:15:45,554 --> 00:15:50,994
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If there's anything that could
decide this race quickly...</b></font>

204
00:15:50,994 --> 00:15:53,834
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It would be Fujiwara losing.</b></font>

205
00:15:53,834 --> 00:15:59,734
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Put another way, unless he digs in for the
long haul, he'll have no chance of winning.</b></font>

206
00:15:59,734 --> 00:16:03,144
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>That's the kind of race
you should think of this as.</b></font>

207
00:16:03,144 --> 00:16:06,744
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The key will be the second round,
when the opponent goes first.</b></font>

208
00:16:06,744 --> 00:16:10,384
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If Fujiwara can hang in there,
tough it out somehow...</b></font>

209
00:16:10,384 --> 00:16:13,544
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>This will become one
tangled marathon of a race.</b></font>

210
00:16:16,024 --> 00:16:21,824
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Anyone with a bit of knowledge
would think that about the first round.</b></font>

211
00:16:21,824 --> 00:16:24,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>No matter how heated things
look like they're getting,</b></font>

212
00:16:24,524 --> 00:16:27,694
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>they're still just trading light jabs.</b></font>

213
00:16:42,514 --> 00:16:44,954
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>--Awesome!
--So fast!</b></font>

214
00:16:44,954 --> 00:16:50,254
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>They're both fast! Joshima of Purple
Shadow and Project D's Eight-Six!</b></font>

215
00:16:50,254 --> 00:16:53,054
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I've never seen such fast cornering before!</b></font>

216
00:16:53,054 --> 00:16:56,554
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It's awesome... An all-out downhill battle!</b></font>

217
00:16:58,034 --> 00:17:00,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>The first round will be over soon.</i></b></font>

218
00:17:00,434 --> 00:17:04,764
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Dammit! He did nothing but pressure me,</i>
<i>and I couldn't do anything!</i></b></font>

219
00:17:07,404 --> 00:17:11,704
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This first round went as planned,</i>
<i>with me getting a good, long look at you.</i></b></font>

220
00:17:17,884 --> 00:17:19,374
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>There they are.</b></font>

221
00:17:23,654 --> 00:17:26,984
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>They're right on top of each other!
There's no gap at all!</b></font>

222
00:17:36,434 --> 00:17:38,674
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Beginning the countdown!</b></font>

223
00:17:38,674 --> 00:17:41,904
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Five... Four... Three...</b></font>

224
00:17:41,904 --> 00:17:43,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Two... One...</b></font>

225
00:17:43,844 --> 00:17:45,474
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Go!</b></font>

226
00:17:55,284 --> 00:17:57,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>It looks like the second round's begun.</b></font>

227
00:17:57,524 --> 00:17:59,114
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah.</b></font>

228
00:18:02,364 --> 00:18:08,764
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This second round is the critical stage, huh?</i>
<i>And we're following this time.</i></b></font>

229
00:18:08,764 --> 00:18:14,434
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Fujiwara's tenacity when coming</i>
<i>from behind really is second-to-none...</i></b></font>

230
00:18:14,434 --> 00:18:19,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>He hasn't lost once from behind,</i>
<i>no matter who he's faced.</i></b></font>

231
00:18:19,844 --> 00:18:24,384
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Still, Keisuke said "if"</i>
<i>Fujiwara can hang in there.</i></b></font>

232
00:18:24,384 --> 00:18:27,844
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>Meaning, he must be facing</i>
<i>an incredible opponent!</i></b></font>

233
00:18:49,004 --> 00:18:52,914
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The S2000 really is a difficult car to master,</b></font>

234
00:18:52,914 --> 00:18:55,914
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but its racing capabilities are second-to-none.</b></font>

235
00:18:55,914 --> 00:19:00,514
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Mr. Toudou says it's even faster
at cornering than an NSX.</b></font>

236
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:04,994
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Having a driver like Toshiya
Joshima behind the wheel</b></font>

237
00:19:04,994 --> 00:19:08,264
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>means there's no way it
could lose to an Eight-Six.</b></font>

238
00:19:08,264 --> 00:19:10,494
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Yeah, I wonder...</b></font>

239
00:19:10,494 --> 00:19:17,504
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Maybe he won't even have to do anything
special, just draw out the car's potential,</b></font>

240
00:19:17,504 --> 00:19:22,044
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and that will be enough to catapult it into
a zone where the Eight-Six can't keep up.</b></font>

241
00:19:22,044 --> 00:19:26,414
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'd like to believe that's how
the second round will be.</b></font>

242
00:19:26,414 --> 00:19:31,414
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>But what's "normal" in a situation
like this isn't normal at all...</b></font>

243
00:19:31,414 --> 00:19:34,954
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Because both drivers are
anything but ordinary.</b></font>

244
00:19:34,954 --> 00:19:39,224
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Especially the driver of that Eight-Six, huh?</b></font>

245
00:19:39,224 --> 00:19:43,794
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>He has a genius-like ability you'd
have to race him to understand.</b></font>

246
00:19:43,794 --> 00:19:48,604
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What's more, it's perfectly suited
for that car, the Eight-Six.</b></font>

247
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:53,534
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>In a sense... he was born for the
purpose of becoming that car's driver!</b></font>

248
00:20:00,944 --> 00:20:02,584
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Its engine is not just an NA,</b></font>

249
00:20:02,584 --> 00:20:08,114
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>it is an F20 capable of
producing 125 hp per liter.</b></font>

250
00:20:08,114 --> 00:20:12,754
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The F20 is a VTEC unit that boasts enough
power output to put racing engines to shame</b></font>

251
00:20:12,754 --> 00:20:15,994
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and most assuredly poses a
threat to Fujiwara. However,</b></font>

252
00:20:15,994 --> 00:20:20,734
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>the S2000's true value lies
in its handling capabilities.</b></font>

253
00:20:20,734 --> 00:20:23,404
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Its mid-front mounted engine</b></font>

254
00:20:23,404 --> 00:20:28,134
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>achieves optimal 50:50
front-to-rear weight distribution,</b></font>

255
00:20:28,134 --> 00:20:31,344
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>and its rigid High X-Bone Frame is such that</b></font>

256
00:20:31,344 --> 00:20:35,084
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>one forgets the car's open-body structure.</b></font>

257
00:20:35,084 --> 00:20:40,654
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>In addition to its compact and lightweight
in-wheel, double wishbone suspension,</b></font>

258
00:20:40,654 --> 00:20:44,924
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>it boasts heightened racing
capabilities exhaustively refined</b></font>

259
00:20:44,924 --> 00:20:50,964
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>through traditional means rather than
a modern electronic control system,</b></font>

260
00:20:50,964 --> 00:20:56,364
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>such that it can even beat high-tech cars
fitted with turbochargers or 4WD.</b></font>

261
00:20:56,364 --> 00:21:00,204
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>However, as a car, it is limited to
the smallest percentage of drivers.</b></font>

262
00:21:02,474 --> 00:21:09,114
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>In other words, you have to be extremely
talented in order to make full use of it?</b></font>

263
00:21:09,114 --> 00:21:13,784
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Experiencing the "limited domain"
that is the S2000 is, one could say,</b></font>

264
00:21:13,784 --> 00:21:18,394
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>the privilege of a handful of
drivers blessed with great skill.</b></font>

265
00:21:18,394 --> 00:21:22,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>And "God Arm"Toshiya
Joshima is one such driver.</b></font>

266
00:21:22,524 --> 00:21:26,524
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Fujiwara's gone head-to-head with
a really troublesome opponent...</b></font>

267
00:21:55,264 --> 00:21:59,194
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'm pretty interested in this second round.</b></font>

268
00:21:59,194 --> 00:22:03,164
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>We'll get the general idea of what
kind of script Jo's thought up for this.</b></font>

269
00:22:03,164 --> 00:22:05,104
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>You say "script," but...</b></font>

270
00:22:05,104 --> 00:22:10,404
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Mr. Joshima is in front, so why not just
lose his opponent and be done with it?</b></font>

271
00:22:10,404 --> 00:22:15,544
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Nah. You wouldn't think it,
but he's actually a bit perverse.</b></font>

272
00:22:15,544 --> 00:22:21,574
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>The more talented his opponent, the more
that little devil of his comes out.</b></font>

273
00:22:23,224 --> 00:22:26,424
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>If Jo put his mind to it
and went on the offensive,</b></font>

274
00:22:26,424 --> 00:22:29,694
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I bet he could outdistance <i>any</i> opponent.</b></font>

275
00:22:29,694 --> 00:22:32,634
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Whatever else, he knows
this course inside and out.</b></font>

276
00:22:32,634 --> 00:22:35,694
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Not even a pro racer could
beat us in that respect.</b></font>

277
00:22:45,044 --> 00:22:48,944
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>This is tough. I'm trying my hardest,</i>
<i>but he's still a good distance ahead.</i></b></font>

278
00:22:53,984 --> 00:23:00,794
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I'll say this for the sake of Jo's reputation.
If there's no winner in this second round,</b></font>

279
00:23:00,794 --> 00:23:04,994
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>I think the script he's planned
is to win not when he's leading,</b></font>

280
00:23:04,994 --> 00:23:06,834
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>but when he's following.</b></font>

281
00:23:06,834 --> 00:23:11,004
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>What?! Even for Mr. Joshima,
that would be impossible!</b></font>

282
00:23:11,004 --> 00:23:14,234
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>This course has no straight
angles and is all corners,</b></font>

283
00:23:14,234 --> 00:23:16,674
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>so overtaking someone would be...</b></font>

284
00:23:16,674 --> 00:23:21,244
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>Nah, I bet that's probably
what he intends to do.</b></font>

285
00:23:21,244 --> 00:23:23,234
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b>'Cause he's perverse.</b></font>

286
00:23:41,664 --> 00:23:44,534
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>I didn't notice when I was in front...</i></b></font>

287
00:23:44,534 --> 00:23:46,834
<font face="Open Sans Semibold" size="73"><b><i>...but his lines are different!</i></b></font>

288
